Experiment-4:
-------------
create a food delivery website where user can order food from as particular restaurant listed in the website for handling http requests and responses using nodejs

Aim: The aim of this experiment is to understand how to handle user HTTP Get requests on the  food deliver app to display the list of restaurants & its menu & then how to handle POST HTTP requests to place the orders on the menu of restaurants using NodeJs & ExpressJs

Recommended Hardware/Software Requirements:
-------------------------------------------
->Intel Based Desktop PC with minimum of 166 MHZ or faster processor with at least 64 MB RAM and 100 MB free disk space
->Nodejs, Visual Studio Code

Application setup:
------------------
It is a simple food delivery website backend using Node.js + Express that handles HTTP requests and responses.

Users can:

=>View restaurants

=>View food items from a particular restaurant

=>Place an order

Project Setup:
--------------
mkdir food-delivery
cd food-delivery
npm init -y
npm install express body-parser

Folder Structure:
-----------------
food-delivery/
